  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 2:15-20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The shepherds go to Bethlehem",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "διέλθωμεν δή",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", come! let us go. The force of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δή",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", a highly emotional particle (the second time we have met with it, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "vide",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 13:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), can hardly be expressed in English. The rendering in A. V[24] (and R. V[25]), “Let us ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "now",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " go,” based on the assumption that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δὴ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " has affinity with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἤδη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", is very tame, giving no idea of the mental excitement of the shepherds, and the demonstrative energy with which they communicated to each other, comrade-fashion, the idea which had seized their minds. “The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δὴ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " gives a pressing character to the invitation,” Godet. Similarly Hahn = “agedum, wohlan, doch”. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Cf.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "δὴ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 13:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "διὰ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "διέλθωμεν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " suggests the idea of passing through the fields.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἕως",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (conjunction used as a preposition) may imply that it was a considerable distance to Bethlehem (Schanz).—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ῥῆμα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", here = “thing” rather than “word”.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[24] Authorised Version.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
