  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Vincent's Word Studies",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The shepherds",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Some texts add οἱ ἄνθρωποι, the men; but the later texts omit.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Let us go (διέλθωμεν)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The preposition διά, through, implies through the intervening space.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Thing (ῥῆμα)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "See on Luke 1:37. The utterance of the shepherds contains a climax: \"Let us go and see this saying, which has come to pass; which the Lord made known.\" ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "See on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Luke 1:37",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The utterance of the shepherds contains a climax: \"Let us go and see this saying, which has come to pass; which the Lord made known.\" ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
